I'm considering writing a proper article about political philosophy in games and get a degree in it, just so that I can go in the papers and tell fearmongers to shut up every time some shit stirs up. The more restrictions these idiots (jack thompson for instance) try to impose, the harder it gets to make good games.

@AlphaFirefly 

Well, to put it simply, the ending was a clusterfuck. The main thing is that as things begin to unravel, what is real, what is fake, what is true, what is a lie, becomes blurred for Raiden. Who should he listen to? Is it better to let an elite rule with their wisdom, or should you fight this even though civilians might suffer. What if the entire infrastructure would fall?

The ending of MGS2 becomes a battle for convincing Raiden. Snake already knows too much to be convinced.
